Description:
    Provides a domain-neutral framework for the analysis and visualization of
    discrete-event, agent-based, and node-actor simulation outputs. Designed as
    a general-purpose toolkit for systems where entities (actors, nodes, agents)
    move through states and interact within spatial or network environments.
    Primary application: MEDTACS-SIM military medical simulation (casualty
    flow, IHL compliance, UAV autonomy trade-offs, doctrine effects).
    Extensible to epidemiology, logistics, evacuation, and social dynamics.
    Includes an interactive Shiny dashboard and manuscript-ready export
    functions for Springer Nature journal templates.
